es, and other carriers, and through contacts with trade organizations. Assists with housing, coordinating arrangements, and more. Fill out the <b><a href="/content/index.cfm?pagePkey=39">RFP</a></b> or e-mail <a href="mailto:nytourism@nycvisit.com">nytourism@nycvisit.com</a>. <br /><br />Rhianna Quinn Roddy, VP Global and Domestic Tourism: 212/484-1245<a name="consales"><br /><b><br />Convention Sales</b> <br />Sells New York as a total convention product for accommodations and meeting venues, exhibit facilities, convention services, transportation, attractions, shopping, and dining. Fill out an <b><a href="/content/index.cfm?pagePkey=23">RFP</a></b> or e-mail <a href="mailto:nyserv@nycvisit.com">nysales@nycvisit.com</a>. <br /><b><a name="conser"><br />Convention Services</b> <br />Serves as primary NYC & Company contact to service travel and tourism industry personnel following site selection of New York City. Actively develops sales leads and referrals for appropriate member businesses and brings forth all available NYC & Company resources that can contribute to a successful New York experience. Fill out an <b><a href="/content/index.cfm?pagePkey=23">RFP</a></b> or e-mail <a href="mailto:nyserv@nycvisit.com">nyserv@nycvisit.com</a>. <br /><br />Links groups and F.I.Ts with NYC businesses; coordinates the VIP Delegate Pass <br /> <br /><b>Conference Express</b> <br />Conference Express is a service to event planners who need assistance with placing small meetings and special events that require 199 or fewer sleeping rooms. Requests are distributed to hotels and venues within 24 hours of the time of receipt, requesting that rates and availability be sent to the client directly. Fax 212/246-6310. <a name="comm"><br /><b><br />Communications</b> <br />Acts as a one-stop-shopping source for information on travel to New York City for media worldwide. Promotes New York City and the products/services of NYC & Company members. Publishes a quarterly newsletter <em>What's New in NYC </em>and creates and maintains up-to-date press information. Assists journalists with where to go, who to contact, and what to cover. Media relations tel. 212/484-1270, fax 212/582-8765, e-mail <a href="mailto:nymedia@nycvisit.com?subject=MEDIA REQUEST">nymedia@nycvisit.com</a>.<a name="major"><br /><br /><strong>Major Events & Promotions<br /></strong><font size="2">Creates, executes and markets popular citywide promotions and events that attract visitors and residents including Restaurant Week, Paint the Town, Broadway Under the Stars and CultureFest. Works closely with producers to create promotions that increase the visibility and reach of annual events in NYC including GRAMMY Awards, Tribeca Film Festival, MTV Video Music Awards, Fleet Week. For more information on Major Events & Promotions, please contact </font><a class="" href="mailto:majorevents%26promotions@nycvisit.com"><font size="2">majorevents&promotions@nycvisit.com</font></a><br /><br />To learn more about the Major Events & Promotions Department <strong><a class="" href="http://www.nycvisit.com/content/index.cfm?pagePkey=914">click here.</a></strong><font size="2"><br /><br /><strong>Corporate Partnerships and Sponsorship<br /></strong>Develops and implements promotional campaigns for corporate partners including American Express and Coca-Cola. A cost effective way to target people visiting, living, or working in NYC is through sponsorship of NYC & Company events and programs. For information on becoming a corporate sponsor of NYC & Company, please contact Natasha Caba, VP, Strategic Partnerships & Marketing at (212) 484-1249 or </font><a href="mailto:ncaba@nycvisit.com"><font size="2">ncaba@nycvisit.com</font></a><font size="2"></font><a name="av"><br /><b><br />Audiovisual Services</b> <br />NYC & Company has a slide library available at our New York office to journalists and member businesses only, and only for noncommercial use. <br />Questions? <a href="mailto:av@nycvisit.com">av@nycvisit.com</a>. <br /><b><a class="" href="http://www.nycvisit.com/content/index.cfm?pagePkey=979" ?>Image Request Form</a></b> for Journalists and Members <a name="pub"><br /><b><br />Publications</b> <br />Produces three official <b><a href="http://www.nycvisit.com/content/index.cfm?pagePkey=11">New York City tourism marketing publications</a></b> that feature information on member hotels, museums, attractions, theaters, stores, restaurants, meeting venues, and service providers. All three are published by Forbes Custom Media. <br /><strong>Inquiries about advertising in NYC & Company’s publications: </strong>Jennifer Galperin, Forbes Custom Media, tel. 212/367-3132, fax 212/367-2509.<br /><strong>To correct</strong> <strong>a listing in a publication (for web corrections, see below):</strong> Alan Binenstock, Forbes Custom Media, 28 West 23rd St., 10th floor, New York, NY 10010, tel. 212/367-4104, fax 212/367-4139. <br /><strong>All other publications inquiries: </strong>Stasha Mills, Director of Publications, NYC & Company, tel. 212/484-1247. <a name="web"><br /><b><br />Web Site</b> <br />If members would like to change their web site listing, they may fill out this <b><a class="" href="http://www.nycvisit.com/_uploads/docs/WebSiteListingForm04.pdf" target="_New">form</a></b>. Note that only NYC & Company members are listed and linked on the NYC & Company web site (except in the Calendar of Events, where nonmembers can submit an event). <b><a href="/content/index.cfm?pagePkey=5"><br />Membership information</a></b>. <br /><strong>Sales inquiries of website related products or services: </strong>Stasha Mills, Director of Publications, 212/484-1247. <br /><strong>General questions about our website or Calendar of Events</strong>: Ada Lio, Web Site Manager, 212/484-1231, <a href="mailto:webmaster@nycvisit.com">webmaster@nycvisit.com</a>.<a name="research"><br /><b><br />Research</b> <br />NYC & Company is the official source of tourism statistics for the city. The research department develops and distributes comprehensive information on NYC domestic and international visitor statistics and monitors the travel industry's impact on New York City's economy. For a sample of statistics, see <a class="" href="http://www.nycvisit.com/content/index.cfm?pagePkey=57">Did You Know? <br /></a><b>Journalists requiring statistics: </b>tel. 212/484-1270, <a href="mailto:nymedia@nycvisit.com?subject=MEDIA REQUEST">nymedia@nycvisit.com</a>. <br /><strong>All others:</strong> tel. 212/484-1221, fax 212/397-1931, <a href="mailto:nyres@nycvisit.com">nyres@nycvisit.com</a>.<br />  
